#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Moving an app folder to a different storage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:7
msgid "Applications folder are (*usually*) located in `/var/www/$appname`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:9
msgid ""
"If an application folder is expected to get bigger because of the amount of "
"data it contains, it might be relevant to move it to another storage (like "
"an external hard drive)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:12
msgid ""
"Here's a summary of how to do this the application wordpress. Here, is is "
"assumed that [you already mounted the external hard-drive](/admin/tutorials/"
"external_storage)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "1. Move the entire wordpress folder to an external hard drive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "mv /var/www/wordpress /media/externalharddrive/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "2. Create a symbolic link"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:22
msgid ""
"So that programs looking for files in /var/www/wordpress will actually take "
"them from the harddrive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s /media/externalharddrive/wordpress /var/www/wordpress\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "3. Tweak permissions (maybe?)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:30
msgid ""
"After this, note that you may need to tweak the permissions of `/media/"
"externalharddrive` so that `www-data` (or the user corresponding to the app) "
"is able to read through the folder... Something like :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chgrp www-data /media/externalharddrive\n"
"chmod g+rx /media/externalharddrive\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/55.moving_app_folder.mdx:37
msgid ""
"(but it depends on your exact setup... Please update this doc page if you "
"figure out what to do exactly)"
msgstr ""
